{
  "stem": "13690.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But at the time that I was going to school, to the Polytechnic, the Jewish organization, the HIAS, the, the American Jewish Congress and Jewish committee were constantly calling upon us to move out-- this was the Korean War-- to get out, because we are standing before a third World War, and they would really like that we should move out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the question was now, where do I go?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, of the grace of God, of course, and of the graciousness of our late President Truman, which I think he was a great humanitarian-- and I have to state, not Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not Roosevelt, I would underline three lines.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because Roosevelt was a great man, and as far as the Depression time, helping the American people, which he did, is right.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as far as humanity is concerned, I would say that Truman was one of the greatest presidents, and, and by establishing the Displaced Persons Act.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And under that act, I was privileged to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Eli came a few weeks later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I arrived in the United States on January 27, 1952, and Eli arrived, I think, a few weeks later.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's a very interesting story, the day of my arrival.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The day of my arrival was very bleak.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a rainy day on January 27.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To arrive in New York was very, very, very uninteresting, especially, where do I go?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What should I do?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my contract was, actually, that I had to go to Philadelphia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I applied to Philadelphia, and I was happy to go to Philadelphia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because Philadelphia, I had a friend there that, that lived in Philadelphia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I want to go to Philadelphia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had nobody somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Of course, I had people, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
